This was taken from Everquest.com at the Harpy's Head Tavern area, author unknown.  It's an excerp of the only aspect of the Combine Empire told in the history of Norrath, as you can see, quite sparse for anything about that time in history.<br>
<br>
<br>
This next period of Norrathean history as it relates to many of the races is the least known. It is surmised by the more knowledgeable historians that while the elder races regrouped and reestablished themselves, a small group of Barbarians were suddenly transformed both physically and intellectually. Most believe this to be the last major and direct act of divine intervention, and perhaps the reason so little is known about this period is that the gods wish it to be so, deciding afterwards that they would have less to do with their creations. In any case, this small and enlightened group were the fathers of the Human race, and they rapidly gained a foothold throughout the lands, studying the lost art of geomancy. The Combine Empire, as this lost race of Humans is called, spread throughout the known world, but then died even more quickly than it grew, and for reasons still unknown. And while they are the ancestors of every Human on Norrath and their relics and ruins still litter the lands from Odus to Faydwer, little history of this period remains.<br>
<br>
Dreamchase  =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/01 11:12:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=431.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/sigpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Combine empire with wizards?</span><hr size=1> The Current history, and what NPCs in game say about the Combine Empire are different.<br>
If you ask some NPCs (Like the ones that have to do with the Hall of Heros) you'll find out that the Combine Empire was actually made up of all races. This is why you see their ruins all over the place. It's also what caused their destruction, and forced reloaction to Luclin.<br>
It appears there was a war between the elder races and the Combine empire. Obviously the Combine empire didn't do so well in the war, because they retreated to Kunark and then left Norrath all together via the Great Conjunction.<br>
Also the Shissar, once a ruthless empire on Kunark, left Norrath through the same methods as the Combine Empire,  and now live on Luclin. These will be the major players on Luclin along with the Vah Shir.<br>
<br>
As for the spells, well, Al`Kabor is behind the Translocation spells. There seems to be a rather long quest that will probably end up with the discovery of a translocate that will send players to Luclin. Remember, there is only 7 months left until it goes live.<br>
